289
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:45,250
I'm impressed with how much
you know about the military.

290
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,333
It's hard for me to believe
you're only a civilian.

291
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:49,625
Well, thanks, Sousuke,
but I'm not that good.

292
00:15:49,708 --> 00:15:52,291
You know a whole lot more
about the military than I do.

293
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:54,916
Well... Maybe I know
a little bit...

294
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:58,583
Huh...?

295
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:03,333
W... What're you doing here?

296
00:16:03,416 --> 00:16:05,625
Kaname! What a coincidence.

297
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:07,791
Huh?!

298
00:16:07,875 --> 00:16:09,541
[KANAME growls]

299
00:16:14,875 --> 00:16:15,708
[BOTH sigh]

300
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:17,875
[KANAME]
Oh, boys?

301
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:19,541
Take this, you perverts!

302
00:16:19,625 --> 00:16:21,583
[BOTH scream]

303
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:25,583
[MALE OPERATOR A]
The missile has landed.

304
00:16:25,666 --> 00:16:27,750
[MALE OPERATOR B]
Commence damage evaluation.

305
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:30,791
[COMPUTER] Destruction
of main target confirmed.

306
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:35,250
Readings indicate massive
fire within blast radius.

307
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:47,083
[KGB CHIEF]
The research facility is ruined.

308
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:49,708
All of the data on the
Whispered has been lost.

309
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:52,375
It will be impossible to
continue our research.

310
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:54,083
[MAN]
My condolences.

311
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:56,333
Too bad you had to
keep the data a secret

312
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:59,500
from the Kremlin,
hidden in that facility.

313
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:02,833
Listen, your contract
is cancelled! You hear me?!

314
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:05,125
[clicking]

315
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,833
[MAN]
You know what that sound is?

316
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:09,375
No.

317
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:13,375
[MAN] It's a DVD. I'm looking
at my screen right now,

318
00:17:13,458 --> 00:17:16,166
and I'm seeing some
interesting numbers.

319
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:20,708
Is it the research data?!
Damn you, when did you get it?!

320
00:17:20,791 --> 00:17:21,958
[MAN]
Since I thought your temper

321
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,291
might get the better of you,

322
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:27,291
I took so me extra measures.
Do svidánija, Chief.

323
00:17:27,375 --> 00:17:29,000
Take care of yourself in prison.

324
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:31,583
Wait! What do you plan on
doing with this data?!

325
00:17:31,666 --> 00:17:34,000
[crashing]

326
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:36,333
[OFFICER]
Chief, the party headquarters

327
00:17:36,416 --> 00:17:39,583
has taken a special interest
in your "side job".

328
00:17:39,666 --> 00:17:40,583
[KGB CHIEF]
What?!

329
00:17:40,666 --> 00:17:41,625
[OFFICER]
They suspected that

330
00:17:41,708 --> 00:17:42,958
you misused
government facilities

331
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:45,333
and brought on a
catastrophic loss.

332
00:17:45,416 --> 00:17:48,166
[KGB CHIEF] Wait, you don't
understand! I'm being framed!

333
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,708
[OFFICER] Save it! You can tell
us the whole story in Lubianka.

334
00:17:51,791 --> 00:17:54,500
[cell phone beeps]

335
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:56,333
[MAN chuckles]

336
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:58,958
[KURZ]
Like a big celebrity

337
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:01,666
that nobody wants for
a girlfriend, huh?

338
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,500
Yeah, I could see that.

339
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,583
Chidori certainly knows
how to throw a punch.

340
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:08,208
I tried to let Kazuma run away,
but he fell off the balcony

341
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:09,916
and got tangled in
the hedges below.

342
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,083
I'm surprised he didn't die,
falling from the fourth floor.

343
00:18:13,166 --> 00:18:14,625
It was a close call for me, too.

344
00:18:14,708 --> 00:18:16,083
I finally managed to escape,

345
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:17,791
but if I had been killed
by the mission objective,

346
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:20,625
I have to wonder how the
Lt. Commander would've reacted.

347
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:22,833
Oh, I can imagine how
it would play out:

348
00:18:22,916 --> 00:18:24,875
Please sign here for
the Sergeant's things...

349
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:27,458
And now we will move on to
the next order of business.

350
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:30,666
Come on, Sousuke. Can't I even
get a little chuckle outta ya?

351
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:32,833
